The paper proposes a novel algorithm for neural architecture search in recurrent neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm involves a combination of recurrent and recursive neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. The paper also evaluates the algorithm's performance on language modelling and sentiment analysis, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper focuses on the dynamic construction of cell structures, which is a topic related to neural network optimization and design (cs.NE).
